<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.286785>
    dc:description "FIGURES 33 – 43. Nasoona asocialis (Wunderlich, 1974) male specimen (from Pulau Tioman, West Malaysia, 33 – 38) and N. crucifera (Thorell, 1895) male specimen (from Tad Fan, Laos, 39 – 43). 33, 39, Embolic division, ectal, 42, mesal. 34, 40, Embolic division without paraconvector, ectal. 35, 41, Paraconvector, frontal. 36, 37, Palpal tibia, dorsal, different aspects. 38, 43, Distal suprategular apophysis, lateral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/286785/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

